# Page skill (pointer)

The canonical, always-current version of this skill lives at [`/skills/page/SKILL.md`](../../skills/page/SKILL.md). Read it in full before acting on a page-level change.

Short summary:

- Stockholm pages always exist as a **Swedish + English pair**. Berlin story pages always exist as a **German + English pair**. Do not edit only one locale unless the user explicitly asks for a single-locale change.
- Adding a page requires shell rows in `page-shell-meta.json` + `docs/meta-texts-catalog.md` (see `skills/page/SKILL.md` — do not use `archive/`); then `STOCKHOLM_SV_EN_PAIRS` / `BERLIN_DE_EN_STORY_PAIRS`, `PAGE_CUSTOM_BODY_PATHS`, `[...slug].astro` imports and `pageBodies` map, new body components under `site/src/components/page-bodies/`, and `navigation.ts` entries.
- **`skills/events/SKILL.md`** may hand off here for a **new event URL** (shells + minimal bodies, then back to events for offers/schema). User **attachments** and **extra illustration**: **`skills/images/SKILL.md`** (ingest §E, pick/wire, compare photo/text to peer pages; add images on your own initiative if the page is text-heavy for its type).
- New on-site image files: `docs/responsive-image-workflow.md` + the images skill (not raw ad-hoc `<img>`).
- After `npm test && npm run build`, run **`skills/seo/SKILL.md` §H** on affected paths; record `§H pass` or resolved issues in the PR. If images changed, consider `skills/performance-check/SKILL.md`.

See the canonical file for the full workflow (edit / add / rename / remove), files touched, locale parity rules, verification details, escalation triggers, and worked examples.
